================================================================
 intercept shim demo shell
================================================================

 The LD_PRELOAD shim at /usr/local/lib/intercept.so redirects HTTP
 calls to the hostnames below into a local handler process, which
 speaks the real wire protocol to a backend in the compose stack.

 Endpoints (all plain HTTP):
   http://mylocal.hello       tiny bash handler
   http://mylocal.shim        this shim's own routes/backends
   http://mylocal.kafka       Kafka
   http://mylocal.redis       Redis
   http://mylocal.mongo       MongoDB
   http://mylocal.postgres    Postgres
   http://mylocal.rabbit      RabbitMQ
   http://mylocal.smtp        SMTP (MailHog; UI at http://localhost:8025)
   http://mylocal.grpc        gRPC helloworld (dynamic via reflection)

   Every endpoint has GET /_info describing its routes and backend.

 Quick tour (up-arrow walks through pre-populated history):
   curl http://mylocal.hello/ping | jq
   curl http://mylocal.shim/routes | jq
   info                                          # /_info from all handlers
   pgq "select now(), version()"                 # shell helper over postgres
   kset foo bar && kget foo                      # redis one-liners
   minsert demo users '{"name":"ada","age":30}'  # mongo insert
   mfind  demo users '{}'                        # mongo find
   kprod  demo 'k1|hello' && kpeek demo          # kafka produce + peek
   rpub   demo 'hi' && rget demo                 # rabbit publish + get
   mail_send '{"to":"you@x","subject":"hi","body":"curl!"}'
   grpc_call helloworld.Greeter/SayHello '{"name":"matt"}'

 Streaming (SSE, -N keeps the stream open):
   curl -N http://mylocal.redis/subscribe/chat            # in one shell
   kpub chat 'hello'                                      # in another
   curl -N 'http://mylocal.kafka/topic/demo/consume?from=earliest'
   curl -N http://mylocal.rabbit/queue/demo/consume
   pglisten demo      # then, from a separate shell:  pgnotify demo 'ping'

 Cross-backend pipe (curl is the glue):
   curl -s 'http://mylocal.postgres/query?sql=select+now()' \
     | jq -r '.rows[0][0]' \
     | curl -s -X PUT http://mylocal.redis/key/last_pg_time --data-binary @-

 Full guided tour:   demo
 Debug routing:      INTERCEPT_DEBUG=1 curl ...

